request.description:
### GET /jobs

This endpoint retrieves a list of jobs.

#### Request

This request does not require any request body.

#### Response

The response will be a JSON object with the following schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "success": {
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "message": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "statusCode": {
      "type": "number"
    },
    "data": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "rows": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "id": {
                "type": "number"
              },
              "description": {
                "type": "string"
              },
              "price": {
                "type": "number"
              },
              "paid": {
                "type": ["null", "string"]
              },
              "paymentDate": {
                "type": ["null", "string"]
              },
              "createdAt": {
                "type": "string"
              },
              "updatedAt": {
                "type": "string"
              },
              "ContractId": {
                "type": "number"
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "count": {
          "type": "number"
        },
        "countPerPage": {
          "type": "number"
        },
        "currentPage": {
          "type": "number"
        },
        "totalPages": {
          "type": "number"
        },
        "hasNext": {
          "type": "boolean"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```

### POST /jobs

This endpoint is used to create a new job.

#### Request

- Method: POST

- Base URL: {{base_url}}

- Body:

    - description (string, optional): A brief description of the job.

    - price (number, optional): The price of the job.

    - ContractId (number, optional): The ID of the contract associated with the job.


#### Response

The response for this request can be described using the following JSON schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "success": {
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "message": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "statusCode": {
      "type": "number"
    },
    "data": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "paid": {
          "type": "boolean"
        },
        "id": {
          "type": "number"
        },
        "description": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "price": {
          "type": "number"
        },
        "ContractId": {
          "type": "number"
        },
        "updatedAt": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "createdAt": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```

### Update Job Details

This endpoint allows the user to update the details of a specific job.

#### Request Body

- `description` (string, optional): A brief description of the job.

- `price` (number, required): The price of the job.


#### Response

The response is in JSON format and follows the schema below:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "success": {
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "message": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "statusCode": {
      "type": "number"
    },
    "data": {
      "type": "object"
    }
  }
}

 ```

### Update Profile

This endpoint is used to update the profile information for a specific user.

#### Request

- Method: PUT

- URL: `{{base_url}}/profiles/:id`

- Body:

    - `lastName` (string, required): The last name of the user.


#### Response

The response for this request is a JSON object with the following properties:

- `success` (boolean): Indicates if the request was successful.

- `message` (string): A message related to the request.

- `statusCode` (integer): The status code of the response.

- `data` (object): An empty object in this case.


#### JSON Schema

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "success": {
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "message": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "statusCode": {
      "type": "integer"
    },
    "data": {
      "type": "object"
    }
  }
}

 ```

### Delete Profile

This endpoint is used to delete a specific profile identified by its unique ID.

#### Request

- Method: DELETE

- URL: `{{base_url}}/profiles/:id`


#### Response

The response for this request is a JSON object conforming to the following schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "message": {
      "type": "string"
    }
  }
}

 ```

The response contains a `message` property indicating the status of the deletion operation.

### GET /admin/best-profession

This endpoint retrieves the best profession based on earnings within a specified time range.

#### Request

- Method: GET

- Base URL: {{base_url}}

- Path: /admin/best-profession

- Query Parameters:

    - start (required, date): The start date of the time range.

    - end (required, date): The end date of the time range.


#### Response

The response for this request follows the JSON schema below:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "success": {
      "type": "boolean"
    },
    "message": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "statusCode": {
      "type": "integer"
    },
    "data": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "total_earned": {
          "type": "number"
        },
        "profession": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```
